<paragraph id="8BE3E64EFFD6FF8C9EFC4D35FE07F955" blockId="61.[151,1437,151,1761]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B9283A5CFFD6FF8C9EFC4D35FE1AF92C" bold="true" box="[199,395,1662,1689]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Natural History.</emphasis>
Habitat: sandy river banks, found perching on bare sand patches 
<quantity id="4CA44BABFFD6FF8C9A5A4D35FB27F92D" box="[1121,1206,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="10.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="1.0">1–20 m</quantity>
from the water (
<figureCitation id="1367FACBFFD6FF8C9B544D35FF26F909" captionStart="FIGURES 14–21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1740,1764]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,186,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-31@6.[161,1427,181,1716]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14–21. Representative habitats of inland sand-perching Lasiopogon species collected for this revision. (14) Washington: Asotin Co., Snake River, sandy bank 4 mi S of Asotin jct Hwy 129, 21.iv.2014 (L. ripicola). (15) Washington: Thurston Co., Tumwater, Deschutes River @ Pioneer Park, 15.v.2015 (L. puyallupi stat. nov.). (16) Oregon: Linn Co., Crabtree Creek @ Hwy 226 bridge 8 mi N of Lebanon, 19.v.2012 (L. willametti). (17) Washington: Franklin Co., Juniper Dunes Wilderness, N entrance, 18 mi NE of Pasco, 20.iv.2014 (L. albidus). (18) California: Marin Co., San Antonio Creek, San Antonio Rd 4.5 mi S of Petaluma, 15.iii.2014 (L. zonatus, L. esau sp. nov.). (19) California: Riverside Co., Little San Gorgonio Creek @ Potrero blvd bridge, 2 mi NW of Beaumont, 9.iii.2014 (L. wilcoxi sp. nov.). (20) New Mexico: Grant Co., Gila River below Forks campsite, 6.v.2015 (L. karli sp. nov.). (21) California: Riverside Co., Santa Ana River at Mt. Rubidoux, 4.iii.2013 (L. drabicolum)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4403141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4403141/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Dates collected: 28 April to 6 May. The asilid 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C9DCDFFD6FF8C9CE74DE9FBA5F909" authority="Wilcox" authorityName="Wilcox" authorityYear="1936" box="[732,1076,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Stichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenicola">
<emphasis id="B9283A5CFFD6FF8C9CE74DE9FC4AF909" box="[732,987,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Stichopogon arenicola</emphasis>
Wilcox
</taxonomicName>
was also flying concurrently in the same microhabitat.
</paragraph>
